Interface QuerySplitter<Q>

    Q - The type of queries to be split.
    All Known Implementing Classes:

    public interface QuerySplitter<Q>
    Interface accepted by Loader for splitting a query into pieces in order to process them asynchronously.
    Author:
    Matthias Fisch

      java.util.Collection<Q> splitQuery(Q query)

    • Method Detail

      • splitQuery

        java.util.Collection<Q> splitQuery(Q query)
        Splits the query into smaller parts that can be processed in separate threads. Used by Loader when splitting a bigger query into parts and delegating processing to workers.
        Returns:
        Collection of query-packages forming the query in union.
